TY  - JOUR
TI  - The General Equivalence of Granger and Sims Causality
AU  - Chamberlain, Gary
AB  - [Linear predictor definitions of causality are not adequate for discrete data. The paper extends the Granger and Sims definitions by using conditional independence instead of linear predictors. The extended definition of "y does not cause x" is that x is independent of past y conditional on past x. This is stronger than the strict exogeneity condition that y be independent of future x conditional on current and past x. Under a weak regularity condition, however, if y is independent of future x conditional on current and past x and past y, then y does not cause x.]
C1  - Full publication date: May, 1982
DB  - JSTOR
DO  - 10.2307/1912601
EP  - 581
